This paper deals with a communication system consisting of sources, a server, and a sink, which is a common topic in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the management of packets, which is a key aspect of information theory (cs.IT). The use of stochastic hybrid systems (SHS) technique suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY). The M/M/1 queueing model is a well-known model in the field of probability and statistics (cs.PF), and the use of numerical methods to evaluate the proposed policy suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of applied mathematics (cs.MA).
